log: Create a Wayang plan that checks the total purchases in 2025 from creditors with "VVS" in their name. It must also be creditors that do not have "SLETTET" in their name. Output in descending. I want creditor_id, creditor name and total price of each in my output. Output in textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log: Create a Wayang plan that reads the purchase records from a dataset/table named "purchases" with at least the fields: creditor_id, creditor_name, purchase_date, and price. Filter records to include only those with purchase_date in the year 2025 and where creditor_name contains the substring "VVS" (case-sensitive match) and does NOT contain the substring "SLETTET". Group the filtered records by creditor_id and creditor_name, compute the total price per creditor (sum of price) as total_price, and produce output rows containing creditor_id, creditor_name, and total_price. Sort the results in descending order by total_price. Write the final result to a text file.

log.thoughts: factpurchases is needed to filter purchases by invoice_date (2025) and sum invoice_line_price per creditor_id. creditor is needed to filter creditor names (contain 'VVS' and not contain 'SLETTET') and to return creditor_id and name for the output. No text input files are required.

steps.detailed_description: Load the tables factpurchases and creditor as inputs. Use factpurchases columns including creditor_id, invoice_date, and invoice_line_price (these correspond to the user's purchase records' purchase_date and price). Use creditor table to obtain creditor.name (this corresponds to creditor_name). Keep all relevant columns for later processing.

Join factpurchases with creditor on factpurchases.creditor_id = creditor.creditor_id to produce a combined dataset that includes: creditor_id, creditor.name (as creditor_name), invoice_date (the purchase date), and invoice_line_price (the price). Output: enriched purchases with creditor_name and price columns.

Apply the following sequence of transformations to the joined dataset: (a) Filter rows where invoice_date falls in the year 2025 (i.e., invoice_date >= '2025-01-01' and invoice_date <= '2025-12-31'). (b) Filter rows where creditor.name contains the substring 'VVS' (case-sensitive) and does NOT contain the substring 'SLETTET'. (c) Group the remaining rows by creditor_id and creditor.name (use creditor.name as creditor_name) and compute the sum of invoice_line_price as total_price. (d) Produce result rows with columns creditor_id, creditor_name, total_price. (e) Sort the result in descending order by total_price.
Write the final sorted result (creditor_id, creditor_name, total_price) to a text file as the requested output.

log.thoughts: Read both tables, join to get creditor_name, then filter by date and name, aggregate and sort, and finally write output. Four steps (input, join, unary pipeline, output) capture the necessary high-level subtasks.
